dfischer.utils

Class PerformanceDataCurve

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.PerformanceDataCurve

  • public class PerformanceDataCurve
extends java.lang.Object
    Aggregates several load test results from the same load test program to a common statistic. This class expects that one or more load test results - executed with a different number of concurrent users - are first added by using the method addPerformanceData() before any statistic method is called.

    • Method Detail

      • addPerformanceData

        public void addPerformanceData(PerformanceData performanceData)
        Adds a load test result of a test run to the common statistic data. Only test (results) with a different number of concurrent users should be added. This method is commonly called more than once before the common statisic is examined.
        Parameters:
        performanceData - measured performance data of a single test run.

      • getPerformanceData

        Returns:
